page.title: 14A School-girl's Diary (1)
page.content: I usually get up at eight o'clock. I get washed and brush my teeth and then get dressed.I'm usually down stairs by ten past eight and then I have my breakfast.At about quarter past eight I put my socks and shoes on. I watch telly and then I go out at about twenty five minutes past eight.I call for Jackie Grayson and we set off at about twenty to nine.I usually arrive at school at quarter to nine.At five to nine the bell goes and we go into school.Then the register is done and at about ten past nine we go down to assembly.We usually get back from assembly at half past nine.Then we start work and we usually do S.M.P. At ten thirty we have a playtime.At playtime I walk around the yard.Our playtime ends at quarter to eleven. We work till eleven thirty and then we go for French.
